title: Australia Bankruptcies
description: Bankruptcies in Australia decreased to 643 Companies in September from 692 Companies in August of 2022. Bankruptcies in Australia averaged 644.79 Companies from 1999 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 1123 Companies in February of 2012 and a record low of 192 Companies in January of 2021. In Australia, bankruptcies account for insolvent corporations who cannot repay their debts to creditors and carry on with their business. This page provides - Australia Bankruptcies - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Australian Securities and Investments Commission
